"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-02-france-argentina-players-clash-pitch-tense-olympic-football-match-21352645\", \"text\": \"France and Argentina's players clashed after the full-time whistle of theirOlympicsfootball match amid high tensions between the two nations.  Hosts France sealed a 1-0 win over their bitter rivals on Friday night, courtesy of Jean-Philippe Mateta's bullet header in the sixth minute.  Thierry Henry's side advance to the semi-finals where they will face Egypt, with the victor going on to play either Spain or Morocco in the final.  Tensions between the two teams have been a boiling point after members of Argentina's triumphant Copa America squad were filmedsinging a racist and transphobic chantaimed toward the French.  Chelsea's Enzo Fernandez streamed the video on Instagram which has been widely condemned, with his club teammate and France star Wesley Fofana describing it as'uninhibited racism'.  The chant was first sung by Argentina fans following their victory over France in the 2022 World Cup final.  Fight breaks out between France and Argentina after their Olympics match tonight!  \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0098\\u00b3https://t.co/RnqLWUlW0K  Metro's Head of Sport James Goldman delivers punchy analysis, transfer talk and his take on the week's biggest stories direct to your inbox every week.  Sign up here, it's an open goal.  French fans booed and jeered Argentina's squad at the Nouveau Stade de Bordeaux before and during the match, though players managed to get through the 90 minutes in one piece.  That all changed after the full-time whistle however, with celebrations for Les Bleus turning ugly as several opposition players confronted them, sparking a melee on the pitch.  Argentine captain Nicolas Otamendi appeared to be heavily involved, though ESPN report it was Enzo Millot who sparked the fight after he celebrated in the faces of his rivals.  Players were quickly separated and ushered down the tunnel, before the France team later re-emerged to applaud their fans.  Speaking after the chaos, Henry admitted he 'did not like' what he saw and was furious that Millot was sent off by the referee for his part in the brawl.  'I do not agree with what happened at the end of the match. My player [Millot] got a red card and\\u00a0I do not accept it, it should not happen,' the France and Arsenal legend said.  'I could not control what happened. I went to greet the coach and when I turned around, what happened happened.  'We won, but I did not like what happened at the end with my player.'  For more stories like this,check our sport page.  Follow Metro Sport for the latest news onFacebook,TwitterandInstagram.  ArrowMORE:Olympic swimmer breaks silence after collapsing by pool after race  ArrowMORE:Olympics opening ceremony drag queen sues Laurence Fox for 'evil' comments  ArrowMORE:Team GB star Kye Whyte taken to hospital after horror BMX crash at Paris Olympics  Sign up and tell us which team you support to get personalised updates about your club.  Select your team for football news tailored to youClose  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy\"}"